#create a function to identify which character are a country flag emoji
def num_flag_emoji(text):
    num_country_emoji =0
    for c in text:
        if "\U0001F1E6\U0001F1E8" <= c <= "\U0001F1FF\U0001F1FC" or c in ["\U0001F3F4\U000e0067\U000e0062\U000e0065\U000e006e\U000e0067\U000e007f", "\U0001F3F4\U000e0067\U000e0062\U000e0073\U000e0063\U000e0074\U000e007f", "\U0001F3F4\U000e0067\U000e0062\U000e0077\U000e006c\U000e0073\U000e007f"]:
            num_country_emoji += 1
    return num_country_emoji

PRETRAINED_MODEL_PATH = "C:\\Users\\merre\\Desktop\\lid.176.bin"
model = fasttext.load_model(PRETRAINED_MODEL_PATH)
df_all['predict_lang']='other'
ii=0

#finds which language is most probable, English or Spanish

for i in df_all["all_text"].replace('[','').replace(',','').replace(']',''):
    sup =[item.replace('\n', '').replace("'",'') for item in re.findall(r'[\s\?\!\"\']+[a-zA-Z\u00C0-\u00FF]+[\s\.\?\!\"\']+',i)]
    sup=[j[0] for j in Counter(sup).most_common(15)]
    model_preds= list(model.predict(str(sup),k=4))
    if str(model_preds[0][0].replace('''__label__''','')) in ['en','es']:
        which_pred = 0
    elif str(model_preds[0][1].replace('''__label__''','')) in ['en','es']:
        which_pred =1
    elif str(model_preds[0][2].replace('''__label__''','')) in ['en','es']:
        which_pred =2
    elif str(model_preds[0][3].replace('''__label__''','')) in ['en','es']:
        which_pred =3
    else:
        which_pred=4
    if which_pred==4:
        df_all['predict_lang'][ii]='es'
    else:
        df_all['predict_lang'][ii]=model_preds[0][which_pred].replace('''__label__''','')
    ii +=1

df_all['new_lang']='es'

#Use the predictions to replace the missing data

for i in range(len(df_all['predict_lang'])):

        df_all['new_lang'][i]= 'en'
    elif str(df_all['defaultAudioLanguage'][i]) in ['','nan','nan ',' ']:
        df_all['new_lang'][i]= df_all['predict_lang'][i]
    else:
        df_all['new_lang'][i]= df_all['predict_lang'][i]

def display_side_by_side(*args,titles=cycle([''])):
    html_str=''
    for df,title in zip(args, chain(titles,cycle(['</br>'])) ):
        html_str+='<th style="text-align:center"><td style="vertical-align:top">'
        html_str+=f'<h2>{title}</h2>'
        html_str+=df.to_html().replace('table','table style="display:inline"')
        html_str+='</td></th>'
    display_html(html_str,raw=True)

def run_xgboost():

    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_data,y_data,test_size=0.2)
    reg_xgb = xgb.XGBClassifier(objective="binary:logistic",n_estimators=80, max_depth=6,learning_rate=.4,min_child_weight=1.2
    ,gamma=.5,reg_lambda=15,interaction_constraints=[[45, 46, 47, 48], [40, 41, 42, 43]],check_additivity=False)   
    reg_xgb.fit(X_train,y_train,verbose=False,early_stopping_rounds=10,eval_set=[(X_test,y_test)])
    explainer = shap.TreeExplainer(reg_xgb)
    shap_values = explainer.shap_values(X_train.reset_index().drop('index',axis=1))
    predictions = reg_xgb.predict(X_test, ntree_limit = 0)
    df_preds = pd.concat([X_test.reset_index(),pd.DataFrame(y_test,columns=["high_views"]).reset_index(),pd.DataFrame(predictions,columns=["preds"])],axis=1).drop('index',axis=1)
    return X_train,shap_values,df_preds

for i in range(100):
    
    if i ==0:
        X_train,shap_values,df_preds = run_xgboost()
        df_all_X_train = X_train.reset_index().drop('index',axis=1)
        df_all_preds = df_preds
        all_shap_values = shap_values
